# UI rules (FigUI3 / PropsKit)

The plugin UI runs in a Figma iframe. PropsKit controls are **[FigUI3](https://rog.ie/figui3) web components**, bundled into a single `ui.html`. Read **`docs/08-figui3-ui.md`** before writing UI ŌĆö it documents why controls fail silently and the exact panel layout.

## File workflow

| Edit | Do not edit |
|---|---|
| `template/src/ui.template.html` | `template/src/ui.html` (generated) |

After UI changes: `npm run bundle-ui` (or `npm run build`), then re-run in Figma.

## Required behavior

1. **Wait for custom elements before init.** Use `Promise.all([customElements.whenDefined('fig-...'), ...]).then(init)`. Never rely on `DOMContentLoaded` alone because FigUI3 may not be registered yet.
2. **Explicit first run (Generators).** Primary **Generate** footer button ŌĆö no canvas output on plugin open. After first run, controls commit-fire `regenerate` **only when a tool output frame is selected** (`outputSelected`). **Generate** always posts `{ type: 'generate' }`; the sandbox adds a new frame when nothing is selected and **must not delete** existing tool outputs. Actions wait for **Apply**.
3. **FigUI3 components only.** Use `<fig-field>`, `<fig-dropdown>`, `<fig-slider>`, etc. Do not use raw HTML with `.propskit-*` classes, shadcn, MUI, or Tailwind. Do not use `<fig-field-slider>`; it is not registered in the bundled FigUI3 build.
4. **Commit-fire.** Bind `change` on controls, never `input` on sliders or text fields.
5. **Receive `loadState`** and rehydrate via `readValue` / `writeValue` helpers (see `docs/08-figui3-ui.md`).
6. **Panel layout.** Use `<fig-group>`, `<fig-header borderless>`, `<fig-footer borderless>`. Preserve the spacing override CSS block from `scaffold/src/ui.template.html` every time. It includes color-picker fixes, so do not strip it when the tool has colors.
7. **Color picker.** If the tool uses `<fig-input-color>`, use `text="true" alpha="true" picker="figma"`. Preserve the scaffold's `dialog.fig-fill-picker-dialog` CSS and popover resize JS. Read **`docs/08-figui3-ui.md > Color picker`**. Never add `min-width` or `width: 100%` on `.fig-fill-picker-input-mode`.
8. **`figma.showUI({ width: 240, themeColors: true, height: ŌĆ” })`** in `code.ts`.
9. **No forbidden words** in UI strings: `plugin`, `Code Object`, `defineProperties`, `Sinatra`, `manifest`, `widget`, `extension`.

## FigUI3 must be inlined

No `<script src="ŌĆ”">` or `<link href="ŌĆ”">` for FigUI3. The build inlines CSS/JS via `<!-- FIGUI3_CSS -->` and `<!-- FIGUI3_JS -->` placeholders. External assets are ignored in the plugin iframe.

## Message-passing pattern

```js
parent.postMessage({
  pluginMessage: { type: 'regenerate', state: getStateFromForm() }
}, '*');

window.onmessage = function (event) {
  var msg = event.data.pluginMessage;
  if (msg && msg.type === 'loadState') {
    setStateInForm(msg.state);
  }
  if (msg && msg.type === 'outputSelected') {
    outputSelected = !!msg.selected;
  }
};
```

**Output targeting (Generators):** `generate` on footer click; `regenerate` only when `outputSelected`. See `docs/07-plugin-practices.md > Output targeting`.

## What NOT to do

- Do not hand-edit `ui.html`.
- Do not use ES module `import` for FigUI3.
- Do not add `body` padding ŌĆö panel is edge-to-edge.
- Do not put section separator pseudo-elements inside `fig-header` (it is a horizontal flex row ŌĆö titles will clip).
- Do not use segmented controls. Use `<fig-dropdown>`.
- Do not introduce tabs, wizards, or modals.
- Do not bind `input` events on sliders.
- Do not post `regenerate` on control change when no tool output is selected ŌĆö that stacks orphan frames.
- Do not remove or rewrite the color-picker CSS block when using `<fig-input-color>`.
- Do not add `min-width` or `width: 100%` on `.fig-fill-picker-input-mode`.

